# Styling

## Tailwind CSS
- Use Tailwind utility classes; avoid custom CSS where possible
- Theme: `data-theme="dark"` / `data-theme="light"` on root
- Use design tokens: `primary`, `secondary`, `muted`, `accent`, `destructive`, `border`, `ring`, etc.
- Border radius: `rounded-lg`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-sm` (map to `--radius`)

## Class Merging
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional/merged classes:
  ```javascript
  <div className={cn('base-class', isActive && 'active-class', className)} />
  ```

## Animations
- Use `tailwindcss-animate` and existing keyframes: `animate-fadeIn`, `animate-slide-up`, `animate-float`
- Custom durations: `duration-150`, `duration-200`, etc. (see tailwind.config.js)

## UI Components
- Use Radix-based components from `@/components/ui/` (Button, Card, Input, Dialog, Tabs, etc.)
- Extend with Tailwind; do not override Radix internals unnecessarily
